# 2021 Map of the Complexity Sciences

<!-- Exported from concept-mapper, 2026-03-27. Based on Castellani & Gerrits (2021). -->

## Decades

| Gen | Period | Label | Notes |
|-----|--------|-------|-------|
| 1 | 1940s–1950s | Origins | Cybernetics, general systems, early computing |
| 2 | 1960s | Expansion | Cognitive science, catastrophe theory |
| 3 | 1970s | Diversification | Self-organization, chaos, dissipative structures |
| 4 | 1980s | Consolidation | CAS, Santa Fe, fractals |
| 5 | 1990s | Network Turn | Small worlds, agent-based models |
| 6 | 2000s | Scale | Scale-free networks, computational social science |
| 7 | 2010s | Application | Applied complexity, deep learning, urban science |
| 8 | 2020s | Convergence | Pandemic modelling, AI-complexity convergence |

## Field Nodes

```
id:               systems_theory
name:             Systems Theory
domain:           systems_cybernetics
decade:           1940s
prominence:       dominant
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1940s–present
key_concepts:     Open systems, feedback loops, homeostasis, equifinality
tags:             foundational, interdisciplinary
notes:            Originated with von Bertalanffy's general systems theory; pervasive influence across all complexity streams
```

```
id:               cybernetics
name:             Cybernetics
domain:           systems_cybernetics
decade:           1940s
prominence:       dominant
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1940s–1970s
key_concepts:     Feedback, control, communication, circular causality
tags:             foundational, information
notes:            Wiener, Ashby, McCulloch — the science of communication and control in animals and machines
```

```
id:               artificial_intelligence
name:             Artificial Intelligence
domain:           ai_cognitive
decade:           1960s
prominence:       dominant
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1956–present
key_concepts:     Symbol manipulation, search, neural networks, machine learning
tags:             computation, cognition
notes:            Dartmouth conference 1956; alternating winters and springs; now converging with complexity
```

```
id:               cognitive_science
name:             Cognitive Science
domain:           ai_cognitive
decade:           1960s
prominence:       major
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1960s–present
key_concepts:     Mental representations, connectionism, embodied cognition, situated cognition
tags:             cognition, interdisciplinary
notes:            Bridging AI, psychology, linguistics, philosophy, neuroscience
```

```
id:               mathematical_complexity
name:             Mathematical Complexity
domain:           math_physical
decade:           1940s
prominence:       major
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1940s–present
key_concepts:     Computational complexity, algorithmic information, Turing machines, Kolmogorov complexity
tags:             formal, foundational
notes:            Formal foundations underpinning all complexity science; Turing, Gödel, Kolmogorov
```

```
id:               catastrophe_theory
name:             Catastrophe Theory
domain:           math_physical
decade:           1970s
prominence:       minor
field_type:       bridging
period_active:    1968–1980s
key_concepts:     Bifurcation, topological discontinuity, fold catastrophe
tags:             mathematics, dynamics
notes:            René Thom; brief intense interest then criticism, but ideas absorbed into dynamical systems
```

```
id:               complex_systems
name:             Complex Systems
domain:           core_complexity
decade:           1970s
prominence:       dominant
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1970s–present
key_concepts:     Nonlinearity, feedback, adaptation, path dependence
tags:             foundational, core
notes:            Umbrella field encompassing many sub-disciplines; Santa Fe Institute as institutional anchor
```

```
id:               self_organization
name:             Self-Organization
domain:           core_complexity
decade:           1970s
prominence:       major
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1960s–present
key_concepts:     Spontaneous order, dissipative structures, pattern formation, autopoiesis
tags:             core, dynamics
notes:            Prigogine's dissipative structures; Haken's synergetics; Maturana & Varela's autopoiesis
```

```
id:               complex_adaptive_systems
name:             Complex Adaptive Systems
domain:           core_complexity
decade:           1980s
prominence:       dominant
field_type:       foundational
period_active:    1980s–present
key_concepts:     Adaptation, fitness landscapes, co-evolution, schemas, building blocks
tags:             core, santa_fe
notes:            Holland, Kauffman, Gell-Mann at the Santa Fe Institute; agents adapting to each other
```

```
id:               emergence
name:             Emergence
domain:           emergence_dynamics
decade:           1980s
prominence:       dominant
field_type:       bridging
period_active:    1980s–present
key_concepts:     Macro from micro, downward causation, strong vs weak emergence, levels
tags:             core, philosophical
notes:            Central bridging concept connecting dynamics, computation, and philosophy of complexity
```

```
id:               systems_dynamics
name:             Systems Dynamics
domain:           emergence_dynamics
